 <title>Why so sketchy? An introduction to sketching</title>
 <link>http://loc.2015.drupal.ie/sessions/why-so-sketchy-introduction-sketching</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-session-date field--type-datetime field--label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;date-display-single&quot; property=&quot;dc:date&quot; datatype=&quot;xsd:dateTime&quot; content=&quot;2015-05-22T13:45:00+01:00&quot;&gt;Friday 22nd, 13:45&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-session-room field--type-text field--label-inline clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Room:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Meeting Room 1&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-session-presenter field--type-entityreference field--label-inline clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Presenter:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/renreilly&quot;&gt;renreilly&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-session-level field--type-taxonomy-term-reference field--label-inline clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Session Level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/categories/session-level/beginner&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;Beginner&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-session-theme field--type-taxonomy-term-reference field--label-inline clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Session Theme:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/categories/session-theme/design&quot; typeof=&quot;skos:Concept&quot; property=&quot;rdfs:label skos:prefLabel&quot; datatype=&quot;&quot;&gt;Design&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-session-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;User Experience Design is a balancing act between user requirements, business needs and technical constraints. Why then, do so many companies only involve their developers in the final stage of their projects? Involving your developers in the UX process from the beginning means they will understand the rationale for the website and the design approach. They are an invaluable source of information and will provide valuable inputs and contributions, which in turn will mean better design decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this hands-on workshop, you will learn about and practice the iterative approach of sketching with pen and paper (controversial). Sketches are quick visual representations of ideas that may lead to solutions. It&#039;s a collaborative technique, which should involve your whole project team. Sketching is not an art and everyone can do it so get onboard with this workshop to improve your Drupal websites. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thank you to everyone who attended the workshop - we had great fun! You can download the slides from the workshop &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dropbox.com/s/5upoq03d1agr7xt/Introduction%20to%20Sketching%20Workshop%20-%20Open%20Days%202015.pdf?dl=0&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. Keep practicing! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
